Annotation.note:
Rectangles $A A_2 B_1 B$, $B B_2 C_1 C$ and $C C_2 A_1 A$ are erected outwardly
on the sides of a triangle $ABC$. Show that the perpendicular bisectors of the
segments $A_1 A_2$, $B_1 B_2$, $C_1 C_2$ are concurrent.
\begin{origin}
Bundeswettbewerb Mathematik 1996, second round
\end{origin}

\begin{keywords}
geometry theorem proving
\end{keywords}
